Nairobi County Women Representative Esther Passaris, Marked 16 Days Of Activism Against Gender Based Violence, In The Company Of SGBV Survivors At The Event Hosted By Matter Catholic Hospital Here In Nairobi. More Than 150 Survivors Of Sexual Gender Based Violence From Mukuru Slums Have Been Receiving Medical And Psychological Care From A Recovery Center Established By The Mission Hospital. The Hospital Has Also Placed Children At Risk In Safe Houses To Deter Further Abuse.